            "type": "text.done",
            "content": "# TCP Three-Way Handshake\n\nThe TCP (Transmission Control Protocol) handshake is a process used to establish a reliable connection between a client and a server before any data is transmitted.\n\n## The Three Steps\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant C as Client\n    participant S as Server\n\n    C->>S: 1. SYN (SEQ=x)\n    S-->>C: 2. SYN-ACK (SEQ=y, ACK=x+1)\n    C->>S: 3. ACK (ACK=y+1)\n\n    Note over C,S: Connection Established ✅\n```\n\n---\n\n### Step 1 — SYN (Synchronize)\n- The **client** sends a segment with the **SYN** flag set.\n- It includes a randomly generated **sequence number** (SEQ=x).\n- This says: *\"I want to connect, and I'll start counting from x.\"*\n\n### Step 2 — SYN-ACK (Synchronize + Acknowledge)\n- The **server** receives the SYN and responds with **SYN-ACK**.\n- It **acknowledges** the client's sequence number: ACK = x+1.\n- It also sends its own **sequence number** (SEQ=y).\n- This says: *\"I got your request, I'm ready, and I'll start counting from y.\"*\n\n### Step 3 — ACK (Acknowledge)\n- The **client** sends a final **ACK** back to the server: ACK = y+1.\n- This says: *\"I got your response. Let's communicate!\"*\n- The connection is now **fully established**.\n\n---\n\n## Why Three Steps?\n\nThe three-way handshake ensures:\n| Purpose | Explanation |\n|---|---|\n| ✅ **Reliability** | Both sides confirm they can send and receive data |\n| 🔢 **Sequence sync** | Both sides agree on initial sequence numbers |\n| 🔁 **Bidirectional** | Communication is verified in **both directions** |\n\n---\n\n## Connection Termination (4-Way)\nClosing a TCP connection requires a **four-way handshake**:\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant C as Client\n    participant S as Server\n\n    C->>S: FIN\n    S-->>C: ACK\n    S-->>C: FIN\n    C->>S: ACK\n\n    Note over C,S: Connection Closed ✅\n```\n\nThis is separate because each side must independently close its half of the connection.\n\n---\n\n## Key Flags Summary\n| Flag | Meaning |\n|---|---|\n| **SYN** | Synchronize / initiate connection |\n| **ACK** | Acknowledge receipt |\n| **FIN** | Finish / close connection |\n| **RST** | Reset / abort connection |\n\nIn short, the TCP handshake is a **mutual agreement** between two parties to ensure a stable, ordered, and reliable communication channel before any real data flows."
          }
        },
